cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the use of computer vision and machine learning techniques to diagnose skin conditions, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The comparison of machine performance with human dermatologists suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the use of publicly available datasets and the discussion of limitations and sources of errors suggest relevance to the medical informatics (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
